15/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Ilinden army barracks on Thursday (14 July) hosted a celebration for soldiers returning from a stint in Iraq, where they participated in Operation Iraqi Freedom. 
Defence Minister Jovan Manasijevski and Army Chief of Staff General Miroslav Stojanovski congratulated them for the assistance they provided to coalition forces in establishing democratic institutions. 
They were the 4th Macedonian contingent to serve in Iraq. 
(Macedonian Government Web site, MIA - 14/07/05)
